All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ActivityLogger
    This class is for logging user login activity to a text file in the project source directory.
    AddAppointmentController
    Controller dedicated to generating the add appointment scene, allowing input from user for new appointment, running user inputs through input validation, and saving the new appointment to the database and local cache before navigating the user back to the main apppointments view.
    AddCustomerController
    Controller dedicated to generating the add customer scene, allowing input from user for new customers, running user inputs through input validation, and saving the new customer to the database and local cache before navigating the user back to the main customers view.
    Alerts
    Class used for generating simple alerts used throughout application
    Appointment
    Class object for appointments.
    AppointmentsController
    Main appointments view that contains navigation buttons to other important views, a list of appointments to be viewed by week or month depending on user toggle choice, and which can be selected by a user to by modified or deleted.
    CachedData
    Handles all local data manipulation, imports data from database, contains some static information for easier maintenance for future developers.
    Contact
    Class object for contacts.
    Country
    Class object for countries.
    Customer
    Class object for customers.
    CustomersController
    Main customers view that contains navigation buttons to other important views, a list of customers to be viewed, and which can be selected by a user to by modified or deleted.
    Database
    Houses connection settings needed to connect to WGU database, connects and disconnects to database.
    DateFormatter
    Class for formatting dates to simple format, converting to UTC
    Division
    Class object for divisions.
    EditAppointmentController
    Edit appointment view that loads the selected appointment from the main appointments page and populates all inputs for that selected appointment.
    EditCustomerController
    Edit customer view that loads the selected customer from the main customers page and populates all inputs for that selected customer.
    InputValidation
    Class for input validations to be done when adding or editing appointments and customers.
    MainLoginController
    Initial view on startup that allows a user to enter login information, validates the inputs, and grabs the relevant user info if successful.
    Paths
    This class holds all the static paths needed for navigating through the differents scenes in the application and provides a centralized source for easier maintenance for future developers.
    ReportAppointmentTypeMonthController
    Initial reports view that also generates the report for appointment types for the chosen month and handles selection/navigation to other types of reports.
    ReportContactScheduleController
    Report view that generates the report for contact schedules and handles selection/navigation to other types of reports.
    ReportCustomerScheduleController
    Report view that generates the report for customer schedules and handles selection/navigation to other types of reports.
    SchedulingApplication
    Creates initial scene/stage and loads main login form
    Text
    This class holds all the static text needed for generating error messages, labels, titles, etc in the application and provides a centralized source for easier maintenance for future developers.
    User
    Class object for user.
